{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "3e0f1eae-c75c-4bcd-bef0-80ee4b49819a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "clustering algorithms:\n",
    "it is one of the unsupervised algorithm  technique which is used to group the data into similar\n",
    "data points where we can identify the patterns"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "02939a43-5f8c-456a-bca0-b1d5f4061366",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "it is mainly used to divide the dataset into similar groups\n",
    "here we need to make sure that the data points in same cljuster are more similar to each other\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "c4042493-2c8b-41ea-a74f-796414bed782",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "use cases:\n",
    "customer segmentation\n",
    "fraud detection\n",
    "recommendation engines"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "c31e0fc8-8ad0-4add-84a8-2f31befd8a4c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Types of clustering algorithms:\n",
    "1.K-means clustering\n",
    "2.Hierarchical clustering\n",
    "3.DBSCAN(density based spatial clustering of application with noise)\n",
    "4.GMM(gaussian mixture models)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "3ef1d210-8652-440f-bf09-d50d2011517a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "K means:\n",
    "it is mainly used to group the similar data points\n",
    "\n",
    "choose the number of clusters(k value)\n",
    "we need to find the similar data by using the euclidean distance formula\n",
    "and then assigns the centroid point\n",
    "and each point find the nearest centroid\n",
    "updates the centroid points repeatedly"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "6b7a697d-a67c-4aff-985c-20545c3143fb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "characteristics:\n",
    "fast\n",
    "easy to understand\n",
    "to find the cluster(k) we can use the wcss(elbow method)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "4a26fe98-8147-47f3-887c-4e663acccb10",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "hiearchical clustering:\n",
    "it is also called as HCA\n",
    "it looks like tree-like structure and also called as dendrogram\n",
    "it consists of mainly two types:\n",
    "1.agglomerative clustering----bottom-->top\n",
    "2.divisive clustering-----top-->bottom\n",
    "\n",
    "no need to initialize the k value\n",
    "this will be helpful for small datasets"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "e87a32f6-3de3-45a9-9c6c-01173c040eaa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "DBSCAN:(density based spatial clustering of application with noise)\n",
    "it is one of the unsupervised learning algorithm which is used to make the similar data points\n",
    "on high density and marks the points in the low density\n",
    "it helps to detect the outliers automatically\n",
    "parameters:\n",
    "eps(radius and distance threshold)\n",
    "minpts(minimum number of points to form a dense region)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "e897f952-4903-4dbb-8423-24191931a71f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "GMM(Gaussian mixture models):\n",
    "it is used to perfrom the probability distribution\n",
    "it assigns each point to a single cluster based on the centroid points"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "71f3f220-80e7-44f4-a2c2-95596b1489b7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Evaluation metrics of clustering:\n",
    "silhouette\n",
    "davies bouldin\n",
    "calinski harabasz"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "a067a540-3dd9-447a-855d-c247671f2243",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "silhouette:\n",
    "it is a metric which is used to evaluate the quality of clusters\n",
    "if the silhouette score is close to +1 then we can understand that it is good cluster\n",
    "if the silhouette score is around to 0 we can understand that the clusters overlap\n",
    "if the silhouette score is close to -1 it is a poor cluster"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "dc37a0ea-42f6-4658-b416-1311d1a8645c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "davies bouldin:\n",
    "it is used to calculate as the average similarity measure of each cluster\n",
    "\n",
    "0 to 0.5---->good clustering model\n",
    "0.5 to 1--->reasonable\n",
    ">1--->clusters may be overlapping or poorly separated"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "3c41d6cc-a66d-43cb-b3a6-f668436882d5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "calniski harabasz:\n",
    "it helps to measure how similar an object is to its own cluster\n",
    "\n",
    "if you have high ch score then it will be considered as a better model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "87e253f2-d20f-4775-81d1-6aa74d730dfa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Assignment:\n",
    "\n",
    "k means clustering mathematical implementation\n",
    "hiearchical clusters how it works\n",
    "dbscan implementation and importance of dbscan\n",
    "what is gmm how it works\n",
    "what are the evaluation metrics used for clustering algorithms"
   ]
  }
